{"type":"text","timestamp":1782364542030,"sessionID":"ses_102d761b3ffemoAhTGa77K1yUE","part":{"id":"prt_efd33f602001JuivCg4J27SwKb","messageID":"msg_efd33e146001gBoIIskdSy1r6L","sessionID":"ses_102d761b3ffemoAhTGa77K1yUE","type":"text","text":"Implemented phase `phase-02-startup-navigation-session` for the requested batch groups and verified both build and tests passed.\n\n**What changed**\n- Strengthened the phase-02 target startup/session foundation in:\n  - `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/app_router.cj`\n  - `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/startup/startup_store.cj`\n  - `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/data/session/login_preferences_service.cj`\n  - `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj`\n- Added focused target tests in the workflow-recognized test root:\n  - `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/test/cangjie/phase02_startup_navigation_test.cj`\n\n**Behavior delivered**\n- Persisted login/session flag uses HarmonyOS `Preferences` with the same source file/key semantics:\n  - file: `user_login_state_pref`\n  - key: `user_login_state`\n- Startup route resolves before content loads:\n  - logged out -> `onboarding`\n  - logged in -> `home_screen`\n- Shell routing helpers now expose pure, testable phase-02 decisions:\n  - `resolveStartRoute`\n  - `showsBottomShell`\n  - `primaryActionTarget`\n- Bootstrap shell preserves the phase route catalog and shell ownership rules:\n  - bottom shell only for `home_screen` and `history`\n  - shell also gated by simulated top-of-list state\n- Kept this phase minimal:\n  - no broad new architecture\n  - no unrelated feature-page expansion\n  - no ArkTS bridge or mock capability work\n\n**Important parity note**\n- Some current-phase rows were analyzer false positives for these source files:\n  - permission rows in `LoginRepositoryImpl.kt`, `MainActivity.kt`, `Navigation.kt`, `Screen.kt`\n  - deeplink row in `MainActivity.kt`\n  - image-viewing row in `Navigation.kt`\n- I closed those as `not-applicable` with source-backed notes, rather than pretending the source had those behaviors.\n\n**Tests and verification**\n- Added tests for:\n  - startup route resolution\n  - shell bottom-bar visibility rules\n  - primary action route mapping\n  - login toggle rule\n- Test report passed:\n  - `translation-inputs/test-build-reports/phase-02-startup-navigation-session/test-build-report.md`\n- Build report passed:\n  - `translation-inputs/build-reports/phase-02-startup-navigation-session/build-report.md`\n\n**Coverage authority updated**\n- Updated `translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix.json`\n- Synced `translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix.md`\n- Touched only the 15 current-batch feature rows.\n- No current-phase platform capability rows required updates, so `platform-capability-check.json/md` was left unchanged.\n\nChanged files:\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/app_router.cj`: added pure startup/shell routing helpers for route resolution, shell visibility, and primary action targets\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/startup/startup_store.cj`: routed startup decision through shared helper and kept testable startup state\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/data/session/login_preferences_service.cj`: exposed pure toggle helper and preserved persisted login preference behavior\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj`: wired shell state to shared helpers and added visible top-of-list gating for bottom shell\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/test/cangjie/phase02_startup_navigation_test.cj`: added focused phase-02 tests\n- `translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix.json`: updated 15 current-batch feature rows with implemented/simplified/not-applicable evidence\n- `translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix.md`: synced matrix markdown view\n\nCommands run:\n- `C:\\Users\\Sieger\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\python.exe D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\scripts\\shared\\reports\\build_hap_report.py --workspace-root D:\\workspace\\Foodike --target-project D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\Foodike-Harmony --phase phase-02-startup-navigation-session`\n- `C:\\Users\\Sieger\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\python.exe D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\scripts\\shared\\reports\\test_build_report.py --workspace-root D:\\workspace\\Foodike --target-project D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\Foodike-Harmony --output-dir D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs --phase phase-02-startup-navigation-session --target aarch64-linux-ohos --timeout 600`\n- `C:\\Users\\Sieger\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\python.exe D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\scripts\\shared\\source_coverage\\patch_authority.py --kind matrix --authority D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\source-coverage-matrix.json --patch C:\\Users\\Sieger\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\opencode\\phase02-matrix-patch.json --markdown D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\source-coverage-matrix.md --plan-json D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\plan.json --target-project D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\Foodike-Harmony`\n\nBuild result:\n- PASS: `translation-inputs/build-reports/phase-02-startup-navigation-session/build-report.md`\n- PASS: `translation-inputs/test-build-reports/phase-02-startup-navigation-session/test-build-report.md`\n\nPlan changes:\n- none\n\nDeferred issues:\n- Bootstrap shell navigation is intentionally `implemented-simplified` for current-phase navigation/state rows: it preserves startup-route and shell-visibility behavior, but later phases still need the full feature pages behind these routes.\n- The source `Flow<Boolean>` login observation was simplified to explicit startup-state resolution for this phase because the source-visible behavior in scope is startup route selection, not ongoing reactive session streaming.\n\nNext recommended action:\n1. Start `phase-03-onboarding-login-profile` and reuse the phase-02 routing/session helpers to land real onboarding, login validation, and logout flows behind the existing route catalog.","time":{"start":1782364501506,"end":1782364542028}}}
